HEADWORD: Yttro-cerite
<hw>Yt`tro-ce"rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A mineral of a violet-blue color, inclining to gray and white. It
is a hydrous fluoride of cerium, yttrium, and calcium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

